  "text": "To use DSLF, we enforce our data representations be continuous. We therefore adopt a 5D S-LF representation (u, v, d x , d y , d z ) where (u, v) index the vertices (as the origin of the ray) and (d x , d y , d z ) to the viewing angle (as the direction of the ray). We pre-partition the input data into diffuse and view-dependent components and feed the latter into two parallel sub-nets. We add a skip-layer [CITATION_1] ] to combine the final prediction layer with lower layers across finer strides, to conduct prediction under the global structure. To further enhance the network's separability to ray directions, we add an additional layer to connect the direction stream (d x , d y , d z ) with the position stream (u, v) .",
